She even ad libbed a thanks outside of the book.

547
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,500
Only okura and nameko left.

548
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,140
So... Wait...

549
00:25:20,140 --> 00:25:21,410
She went to the cashier.

550
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:22,470
Alright.

551
00:25:22,990 --> 00:25:23,960
Heave-ho.

552
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:26,310
It looks like she forgot.

553
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:29,230
Her mother just added those two.

554
00:25:29,230 --> 00:25:31,230
They were not in the book.

555
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:33,020
It can't be helped then.

556
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:36,460
Paying 2000 and receiving 940 yen back.

557
00:25:36,870 --> 00:25:39,890
It's extraordinary that a 3 year old can do all that.

558
00:25:39,890 --> 00:25:41,790
It is. Truly extraordinary.

559
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:44,080
Drinking cold bancha.

560
00:25:44,860 --> 00:25:47,450
And then she remembers...

561
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,140
Ah...

562
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:52,000
I want to buy nameko mushrooms.

563
00:25:50,700 --> 00:25:52,000
You need nameko?

564
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,470
She remembered.

565
00:25:54,110 --> 00:25:56,640
I will show you to the nameko.
Let's go together?

566
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,640
Right th..

567
00:25:57,310 --> 00:25:58,640
Mom also...

568
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:01,010
Ah, I will also buy okura.

569
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:02,980
She remembered the okura.

570
00:26:03,030 --> 00:26:05,400
She remembered everything.

571
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:08,900
Small nameko would be better.

572
00:26:07,550 --> 00:26:08,900
Small would be better?

573
00:26:09,740 --> 00:26:12,240
Since there are sizes of nameko.

574
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:14,960
The big ones are for stir-frying.

575
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:17,260
But the small ones are good in miso soup.

576
00:26:17,460 --> 00:26:18,750
There are various.

577
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:20,830
Let's go with this one.

578
00:26:19,670 --> 00:26:20,830
This one?

579
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:22,920
Yes, these are good with miso soup.

580
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:25,670
And okura?

581
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:25,670
Okura is...

582
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:27,910
This is the last item. Where are they?

583
00:26:29,170 --> 00:26:31,610
They usually can be found here but are sold out.

584
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:35,280
We don't have anymore today.

585
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:37,280
Will this do?

586
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:41,350
While there were eggs...

587
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:43,820
there were no okura. What a rarity.

588
00:26:45,010 --> 00:26:48,560
That's true. Usually there are okura.

589
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:52,860
The hat on tight. Job well done.

590
00:26:52,860 --> 00:26:54,450
Marvelous.

591
00:26:55,750 --> 00:26:59,340
A suspicious cloud surrounds the mountain.

592
00:27:00,990 --> 00:27:04,740
She talked with many and purchased a lot. Now she only needs to head home.

593
00:27:06,090 --> 00:27:07,000
What's wrong?

594
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,810
She's dawdling.

595
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:13,640
My legs hurt.

596
00:27:13,940 --> 00:27:18,110
The book didn't mention that
the groceries would be heavy.

597
00:27:18,110 --> 00:27:20,730
Or that her legs would hurt.

598
00:27:38,060 --> 00:27:39,960
The road along the rice field.

599
00:27:40,380 --> 00:27:44,480
She's not singing the Tanko-bushi song this time.

600
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:45,890
Do your best.

601
00:27:46,050 --> 00:27:48,590
She's 3. And a big sister.

602
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:54,140
She struggles between wanting to exert herself and wanting to be treated sweetly like a child.

603
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:56,900
Her heart is wavering.

604
00:27:56,900 --> 00:27:58,130
I want to help her.

605
00:27:59,250 --> 00:28:00,850
Did she reach her limit?

606
00:28:01,230 --> 00:28:02,520
But wait...

607
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:04,320
Her tears stopped.

608
00:28:04,320 --> 00:28:06,070
She found something.

609
00:28:07,470 --> 00:28:11,360
What is that? The white thing?

610
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:14,110
That's bad. She spotted our drone.

611
00:28:14,610 --> 00:28:15,710
She spotted the drone.

612
00:28:15,210 --> 00:28:16,160
Stop right there.

613
00:28:16,160 --> 00:28:17,750
She's looking at it.

614
00:28:17,750 --> 00:28:20,540
It goes up and down.

615
00:28:20,540 --> 00:28:24,410
It took her mind off the heaviness of the bag.

616
00:28:24,610 --> 00:28:25,960
Good evening.

617
00:28:26,340 --> 00:28:27,660
Good evening.

618
00:28:27,660 --> 00:28:30,050
An old lady is picking flowers.

619
00:28:30,050 --> 00:28:31,530
Good evening.

620
00:28:31,530 --> 00:28:32,000
Huh!?

621
00:28:32,010 --> 00:28:33,300
Good evening.

622
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:34,650
Ah, good evening.

623
00:28:34,650 --> 00:28:38,440
It's not the afternoon yet but the old lady goes along with it.

624
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:40,370
Which one do you want?

625
00:28:40,370 --> 00:28:41,570
Can I??

626
00:28:41,570 --> 00:28:43,110
I want this one.

627
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:47,330
Pink and orange?
That's pretty.

628
00:28:47,650 --> 00:28:48,810
Do you want only 2?

629
00:28:48,820 --> 00:28:50,880
Thank you.

630
00:28:51,370 --> 00:28:53,250
Thank you very much.

631
00:28:53,540 --> 00:28:56,300
Thanks to you the tears have stopped.

632
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:10,340
Your big sister is doing her best.

633
00:29:15,010 --> 00:29:19,710
As soon as she sees the house
she lets out all the tears she held back.

634
00:29:23,520 --> 00:29:25,520
Mommy.

635
00:29:24,670 --> 00:29:25,520
Yes?

636
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:29,910
Yes?

637
00:29:30,340 --> 00:29:32,040
Welcome home.

638
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,990
Thank you. What's up?

639
00:29:34,510 --> 00:29:35,230
What's up?

640
00:29:35,260 --> 00:29:37,100
The important words to tell mom...

641
00:29:38,930 --> 00:29:41,700
They didn't have okura.

642
00:29:40,450 --> 00:29:41,700
They didn't have okura?

643
00:29:42,380 --> 00:29:44,040
It was bothering her.

644
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:47,100
Then let's make tofu and nameko miso soup then.

645
00:29:47,140 --> 00:29:52,160
She wants to be held like a baby.

646
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:56,120
Mommy. This is a present for you.

647
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:57,380
Thank you for the present.

648
00:29:57,380 --> 00:29:59,490
You brought me a gift.

649
00:29:59,490 --> 00:30:00,820
I'm happy. I'm happy.

650
00:30:00,820 --> 00:30:02,450
Thanks. Thanks.

651
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:04,310
That's right. The picture book.

652
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:06,260
Must complete it.

653
00:30:06,260 --> 00:30:09,760
Mio, tell me how you did it.

654
00:30:09,760 --> 00:30:12,910
I missed you, mom.

655
00:30:12,910 --> 00:30:15,120
Because it was so tough.

656
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:17,150
If you write it here.

657
00:30:17,150 --> 00:30:20,590
And so, a lot was added to the book.

658
00:30:21,060 --> 00:30:23,510
That she cried from loneliness before departing.

659
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:26,860
And that she sang Tanko-bushi with joy.

660
00:30:27,100 --> 00:30:29,560
Or that she received flowers.

661
00:30:29,560 --> 00:30:32,600
And much more.

662
00:30:33,770 --> 00:30:37,670
Mom, you've completed a great book.

663
00:30:39,110 --> 00:30:41,690
Well... It's all thanks to me.

664
00:30:44,430 --> 00:30:46,130
She did well.

665
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:49,370
What a marvelous errand.

666
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:50,790
It's a top score.

667
00:30:49,370 --> 00:30:50,790
A top score.

668
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:55,140
Walking aimlessly at first.

669
00:30:55,140 --> 00:30:59,110
Mother of boys of these ages

670
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:59,660
The she remembered it all and to say thanks.

671
00:31:00,430 --> 00:31:05,630
When she said: "They don't have okura"

672
00:31:06,950 --> 00:31:09,070
She's truly laudable.

673
00:31:09,070 --> 00:31:12,990
I want to go back to those times.

674
00:31:13,090 --> 00:31:14,580
When she asked the shopkeeper

675
00:31:14,580 --> 00:31:17,180
did you give birth to eggs?

676
00:31:17,180 --> 00:31:20,000
That was really funny.

677
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:25,970
Things not written in the book are bound to happen.

678
00:31:27,110 --> 00:31:32,750
During the errand of the youngest of 3 brothers the shop will be thrown into disarray.

679
00:31:33,340 --> 00:31:38,840
Tochi ● Tochigi City

680
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:36,750
Here's a house that likes to keep thing neat and tidy.

681
00:31:37,830 --> 00:31:39,320
Time for cleaning.

682
00:31:39,580 --> 00:31:42,740
Inside the house looks like a showroom.

683
00:31:42,750 --> 00:31:47,630
The mother's philosophy is to put everything orderly.

684
00:31:50,450 --> 00:31:54,900
Everything has its place.

685
00:31:55,630 --> 00:31:56,640
Amazing.

686
00:31:57,620 --> 00:32:02,380
The youngest of 3 at 3 years and 9 months, Masashi.

687
00:32:02,540 --> 00:32:06,750
The other two haven't returned from school.

688
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:08,560
Who wants to help?

689
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:09,750
Alright then...

690
00:32:09,750 --> 00:32:13,350
There's a place in the storage room that she isn't satisfied with.

691
00:32:13,350 --> 00:32:14,590
There is?

692
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:18,710
Listen up Mr. Masashi.
Mama wants another of those baskets.

693
00:32:18,710 --> 00:32:24,900
What if there were 3 or 4 of those baskets here?

694
00:32:24,230 --> 00:32:24,900
Yep.

695
00:32:24,900 --> 00:32:28,520
I see. Measuring it so he can purchase the right size.

696
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:30,670
About this high.

697
00:32:30,670 --> 00:32:31,840
Go and purchase them.

698
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:33,840
About thi...

699
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:33,840
That's right.

700
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:36,040
And adding an errand for the dinner.

701
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:39,180
For remuneration let's get the expensive bluefin tuna.

702
00:32:39,930 --> 00:32:42,160
Does he understand "remuneration"?

703
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:44,350
Toro

704
00:32:43,050 --> 00:32:44,670
Toro (the fatty belly meat of the tuna)

705
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,790
Does he understand toro?

706
00:32:48,450 --> 00:32:51,560
For remuneration (as a reward) he will get toro.

707
00:32:52,670 --> 00:32:56,190
On the way back from the fishmonger there is a home center close to home.

708
00:32:56,190 --> 00:32:59,100
He was asked to buy 3 white baskets.

709
00:32:59,260 --> 00:33:00,670
That's difficult.

710
00:33:00,330 --> 00:33:02,440
Please help your mother in cleaning up.

711
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:03,300
Later.

712
00:33:03,300 --> 00:33:04,420
Later.

