4 year older sister

1373
00:58:16,060 --> 00:58:22,020
I really thought that it was like my relation to my brother and sister.

1374
00:58:22,150 --> 00:58:26,610
The idea that the sister was without any fear.

1375
00:58:26,610 --> 00:58:29,790
While the big sister looks out and is serious.

1376
00:58:29,790 --> 00:58:32,260
She thinks about the bigger perspective?

1377
00:58:30,860 --> 00:58:32,260
That's right.

1378
00:58:33,360 --> 00:58:40,870
I have a big brother and our grandparents really were affectionate with me.

1379
00:58:34,060 --> 00:58:40,360
2 year older brother

1380
00:58:40,870 --> 00:58:45,140
They would take me out every day like department stores

1381
00:58:45,140 --> 00:58:47,580
or Japanese confectionary shops.

1382
00:58:48,280 --> 00:58:51,730
So it's all their fault how I've turned out.

1383
00:58:52,220 --> 00:58:55,600
Fault? Don't you mean thanks to them?

1384
00:58:53,300 --> 00:58:55,600
Yeah, thanks to them.

1385
00:58:55,600 --> 00:58:56,490
Yeah, thanks to them.

1386
00:58:56,490 --> 00:58:58,440
Speaking about grandchildren

1387
00:58:58,440 --> 00:59:00,690
both you, Tokoro, and Ito have them.

1388
00:59:00,690 --> 00:59:02,590
You will do anything they ask you to?

1389
00:59:02,590 --> 00:59:04,590
Of course.

1390
00:59:04,590 --> 00:59:07,100
The heck are you saying?

1391
00:59:07,100 --> 00:59:08,330
The same is true for me.

1392
00:59:07,780 --> 00:59:10,070
Nothing hurts when it comes to grandchildren.

1393
00:59:10,070 --> 00:59:11,400
No matter what they do to you.

1394
00:59:11,400 --> 00:59:13,340
Being hit.. like...

1395
00:59:13,340 --> 00:59:15,210
being stabbed with a toy sword.

1396
00:59:15,210 --> 00:59:17,370
Nothing beats that.

1397
00:59:17,570 --> 00:59:21,380
Nothing hurts.

1398
00:59:22,510 --> 00:59:26,070
Miyagi ● Matsushima City

1399
00:59:22,510 --> 00:59:26,260
The sunrise in one of the three beauty spots of Japan

1400
00:59:27,630 --> 00:59:30,720
Matsushima where you can also see the Shiogama shrine

1401
00:59:30,720 --> 00:59:33,310
a tradition that has been carried on for over 1200 years.

1402
00:59:33,310 --> 00:59:37,940
It's a shrine that draws attraction from all over Touhoku.

1403
00:59:37,060 --> 00:59:39,480
It's this amazing on the first day after New Year.

1404
00:59:39,730 --> 00:59:40,680
It's bustling.

1405
00:59:40,410 --> 00:59:44,120
In the past, only men of the Date clan were allowed to climb this.

1406
00:59:44,120 --> 00:59:48,510
It is here, they will climb these stone steps as their first errand.

1407
00:59:49,020 --> 00:59:50,610
The steps
stretch far here.

1408
00:59:50,610 --> 00:59:52,080
But it's a great view.

1409
00:59:51,490 --> 00:59:57,610
Children aged 3, 5 and 7 have come to visit on this autumn day.

1410
00:59:58,420 --> 01:00:01,770
The boy who will go on an errand lives at a candy shop.

1411
01:00:02,270 --> 01:00:05,340
It's like living in a dream.

1412
01:00:05,740 --> 01:00:08,290
To be surrounded by a ton of toys every day

1413
01:00:08,290 --> 01:00:11,140
Ramune, fugashi and dried apricot sticks.

1414
01:00:09,980 --> 01:00:11,730
It's like heaven.

1415
01:00:11,140 --> 01:00:14,300
The boy to envy is Naoki.

1416
01:00:14,300 --> 01:00:18,770
He's always energetic and his favorite game is to play house.

1417
01:00:20,650 --> 01:00:22,360
The one appearing here is....

1418
01:00:22,940 --> 01:00:24,360
Morning.

1419
01:00:24,360 --> 01:00:26,610
It's his girlfriend, Seina.

1420
01:00:27,040 --> 01:00:30,150
A month older, at 3 years and 11 month old

1421
01:00:30,150 --> 01:00:33,420
they've known each other from birth.

1422
01:00:34,300 --> 01:00:35,990
Let's go.

1423
01:00:36,620 --> 01:00:38,760
Don't go too far.

1424
01:00:38,760 --> 01:00:43,260
We were asked by daddy to visit the shrine and purchase a charm.

1425
01:00:43,430 --> 01:00:44,780
Nao.

1426
01:00:44,780 --> 01:00:46,800
Do you know of any good charms?

1427
01:00:46,880 --> 01:00:49,550
To smoothen things.

1428
01:00:49,780 --> 01:00:51,330
Huh? Ah yeah what was it...

1429
01:00:51,330 --> 01:00:53,090
What type of charm is that?

1430
01:00:52,740 --> 01:00:56,570
To smoothen things.

1431
01:00:53,970 --> 01:00:56,570
To smoothen things? Is there one like that?

1432
01:00:56,740 --> 01:00:59,040
The very popular charm at Shiogama shrine.

1433
01:00:59,040 --> 01:01:02,380
A charm to smoothen things.
Could be useful for the errand.

1434
01:01:02,380 --> 01:01:03,510
A charm to smoothen things.

1435
01:01:03,510 --> 01:01:05,750
- What if you went together?

1436
01:01:04,960 --> 01:01:05,750
- Will you go?

1437
01:01:05,750 --> 01:01:07,720
I could even go by myself.

1438
01:01:07,720 --> 01:01:10,690
No way you could.

1439
01:01:10,690 --> 01:01:11,620
Yes, I can.

1440
01:01:11,620 --> 01:01:13,520
What are ya saying.

1441
01:01:13,520 --> 01:01:14,590
Okay but...

1442
01:01:14,590 --> 01:01:17,890
Can you go along with Seina? The two of you.

1443
01:01:17,990 --> 01:01:20,500
Yeah...

1444
01:01:21,430 --> 01:01:23,580
Here are two charms.

1445
01:01:22,250 --> 01:01:23,580
Hidden mic charms.

1446
01:01:23,680 --> 01:01:25,390
This one.

1447
01:01:24,020 --> 01:01:25,390
Boys prefer blue.

1448
01:01:25,900 --> 01:01:28,810
Huh!? He wants the red one?

1449
01:01:29,090 --> 01:01:31,640
Do you know what's on it?

1450
01:01:31,640 --> 01:01:33,860
Touch yours to Seina's.

1451
01:01:40,400 --> 01:01:41,690
How nice.

1452
01:01:40,400 --> 01:01:42,750
So please get along all lovey-dovey.

1453
01:01:42,750 --> 01:01:44,290
All lovey-dovey.

1454
01:01:45,070 --> 01:01:47,270
The soy sauce shop is at the foot of the shrine.

1455
01:01:47,270 --> 01:01:51,410
they were asked to get round-shaped konjaku called Tama-kon.

1456
01:01:51,410 --> 01:01:57,030
Then it is a 202 stairs climb up Omotesando.

1457
01:01:57,070 --> 01:02:00,270
*It was a hill only men of the Date clan were allowed to climb.

1458
01:01:57,070 --> 01:02:04,500
Mens' climb: The steeper one.
Womens' climb: The least steep one.

1459
01:02:00,270 --> 01:02:02,670
Then they enter the grounds to purchase the charm.

1460
01:02:02,670 --> 01:02:08,650
On their way back they will go down the women's climb.

1461
01:02:08,650 --> 01:02:10,510
Do you know which hill to go up?

1462
01:02:10,520 --> 01:02:12,720
The male climb.

1463
01:02:12,720 --> 01:02:14,280
And what about the return?

1464
01:02:14,290 --> 01:02:15,570
The female climb.

1465
01:02:15,570 --> 01:02:18,020
As expected from a local boy.

1466
01:02:18,020 --> 01:02:21,960
I've started craving dango.

1467
01:02:20,920 --> 01:02:21,960
That's nice.

1468
01:02:21,960 --> 01:02:24,160
Will you then go and buy some?

1469
01:02:22,940 --> 01:02:24,160
Yeah.

1470
01:02:24,160 --> 01:02:28,470
This adds a new errand. Dango, enough for 5.

1471
01:02:28,630 --> 01:02:29,280
Oh my.

1472
01:02:29,520 --> 01:02:31,870
Who will command the male climb?

1473
01:02:30,870 --> 01:02:31,850
Seina.

1474
01:02:31,870 --> 01:02:33,850
Seina will command the steep climb?

1475
01:02:33,850 --> 01:02:35,590
Who will command the female climb?

1476
01:02:34,890 --> 01:02:35,970
I will.

1477
01:02:35,590 --> 01:02:37,720
Nao will? Isn't it reversed?

1478
01:02:37,720 --> 01:02:39,630
Commanding officers do your best.

1479
01:02:39,630 --> 01:02:41,580
Hoping to get along. Smooch.

1480
01:02:46,830 --> 01:02:48,230
Off you go.

1481
01:02:48,230 --> 01:02:49,350
We will rely on you.

1482
01:03:13,910 --> 01:03:15,810
The long-established soy sauce shop.

1483
01:03:16,110 --> 01:03:17,910
Huh? The bamboo blinds are down.

1484
01:03:17,900 --> 01:03:19,170
Here perhaps?

1485
01:03:19,170 --> 01:03:20,470
Is it locked?

1486
01:03:20,470 --> 01:03:21,970
Ah, must be closed today.

1487
01:03:21,970 --> 01:03:23,590
It's before the opening hours.

1488
01:03:24,370 --> 01:03:28,090
They haven't opened? Let's tell mama.

1489
01:03:27,010 --> 01:03:28,090
Too early.

1490
01:03:29,190 --> 01:03:31,630
Nao, please wait.

1491
01:03:31,850 --> 01:03:34,100
Don't run.

1492
01:03:32,610 --> 01:03:34,100
Since they came all the way.

1493
01:03:34,100 --> 01:03:37,600
Ah, we must get the dango first.

1494
01:03:39,690 --> 01:03:41,570
They're running back and forth.

1495
01:03:42,920 --> 01:03:45,310
Will they have enough stamina for the climb?

1496
01:03:47,240 --> 01:03:50,330
Right at that moment the shop is opening up.

1497
01:03:50,460 --> 01:03:51,730
It's good that they went back.

1498
01:03:51,380 --> 01:03:53,600
Huh? It's opening now?

1499
01:03:51,730 --> 01:03:53,280
They were early.

1500
01:03:53,600 --> 01:03:56,220
"Phew, we made it" the camera man thought.

1501
01:03:56,550 --> 01:03:58,120
What do you want?

1502
01:03:58,120 --> 01:03:59,990
I want that.

1503
01:03:59,990 --> 01:04:01,090
Round konjyaku?

1504
01:04:01,090 --> 01:04:02,330
How many do you want?

1505
01:04:02,330 --> 01:04:04,160
The always reliable Seina.

1506
01:04:04,760 --> 01:04:06,830
3 please.

1507
01:04:05,400 --> 01:04:06,830
3? Alright.

1508
01:04:06,830 --> 01:04:08,030
Do you want it in a bag?

1509
01:04:08,030 --> 01:04:10,320
Yes, to go.

1510
01:04:10,320 --> 01:04:11,470
So adult-like.

1511
01:04:11,470 --> 01:04:12,600
She's amazing.

1512
01:04:12,440 --> 01:04:16,540
The Tama-kon steeped in soy sauce are only sold on holidays.

1513
01:04:16,660 --> 01:04:18,110
How nice.

1514
01:04:18,390 --> 01:04:20,930
Smells nice.

1515
01:04:21,330 --> 01:04:22,200
Here.

1516
01:04:22,200 --> 01:04:25,420
I will take the 500 yen. Please wait.

1517
01:04:25,670 --> 01:04:27,780
Since it's cold outside

1518
01:04:27,780 --> 01:04:30,040
please have one each.

1519
01:04:30,040 --> 01:04:33,890
The traditional preparation of konjac that has been steeped in soy sauce.

1520
01:04:34,640 --> 01:04:36,680
Delicious.

1521
01:04:35,460 --> 01:04:37,390
That's right.

1522
01:04:38,630 --> 01:04:42,070
Leaving the soy sauce shop they have a steep climb ahead.

1523
01:04:44,370 --> 01:04:46,020
Kids love to run.

1524
01:04:49,590 --> 01:04:51,310
It was delicious.

1525
01:04:50,840 --> 01:04:51,310
Yep.

1526
01:04:51,310 --> 01:04:53,510
The dango shop is next.

1527
01:04:53,010 --> 01:04:53,510
Yep.

1528
01:04:53,510 --> 01:04:55,280
And the charm.

1529
01:04:55,550 --> 01:04:57,810
This is it.

1530
01:04:57,810 --> 01:04:59,350
202 steps.

1531
01:04:59,350 --> 01:05:00,750
202 steps.

1532
01:05:00,750 --> 01:05:03,440
Just as they said. It's 202 steps.

1533
01:05:03,440 --> 01:05:06,020
Not an easy climb even for adults.

1534
01:05:09,710 --> 01:05:11,230
Are you scared?

1535
01:05:11,230 --> 01:05:12,500
I'm not scared.

1536
01:05:12,500 --> 01:05:14,600
Please hang in there.

1537
01:05:14,600 --> 01:05:15,520
I will.

1538
01:05:15,650 --> 01:05:17,220
He's making her carry it.

1539
01:05:16,730 --> 01:05:18,330
I have no power.

1540
01:05:18,330 --> 01:05:19,590
What about Seina?

1541
01:05:18,950 --> 01:05:20,290
And she's the girl.

1542
01:05:20,290 --> 01:05:22,290
I do have power.

1543
01:05:21,250 --> 01:05:22,290
Where is the power?

1544
01:05:22,290 --> 01:05:24,660
Nao is losing.

1545
01:05:25,340 --> 01:05:26,790
It's a guarding lion-dog.

1546
01:05:26,790 --> 01:05:28,030
Guarding lion-dog.

1547
01:05:28,030 --> 01:05:29,810
But he's still buzzing full of words.

1548
01:05:29,810 --> 01:05:32,280
It's a guarding lion-dog.

1549
01:05:31,560 --> 01:05:33,120
He knows a lot.

1550
01:05:32,330 --> 01:05:35,440
Hurry, let's go up.

1551
01:05:35,440 --> 01:05:37,040
A guarding lion-dog.

1552
01:05:37,040 --> 01:05:39,120
Next let's go this way.

1553
01:05:39,120 --> 01:05:40,670
It's easier to go this way.

1554
01:05:40,670 --> 01:05:41,740
Is it?

1555
01:05:41,740 --> 01:05:44,230
I will climb this way.

1556
01:05:44,230 --> 01:05:45,860
It's smarter the other way.

1557
01:05:46,500 --> 01:05:49,230
It's easier this way.

1558
01:05:49,650 --> 01:05:51,430
It's easy, see!

1559
01:05:50,670 --> 01:05:52,300
It's not easier.

1560
01:05:51,730 --> 01:05:56,290
Nao is climbing the area where people stand to view the portable shrine.

1561
01:05:57,690 --> 01:06:00,710
I'm full of vigor.

1562
01:05:59,190 --> 01:06:00,710
Tough!

1563
01:06:01,860 --> 01:06:03,410
Just a bit more.

1564
01:06:03,410 --> 01:06:04,500
Not even close.

1565
01:06:05,930 --> 01:06:07,970
Seina is climbing the stairs

1566
01:06:07,970 --> 01:06:11,640
while Nao is climbing the area where people stand to view the shrine.

1567
01:06:11,640 --> 01:06:13,470
I'm full of vigor.

1568
01:06:14,870 --> 01:06:17,560
The 202 step climb to Shiogama shrine.

1569
01:06:17,560 --> 01:06:20,830
It would even exhaust adults.

1570
01:06:21,150 --> 01:06:22,630
Wait. Don't leave.

1571
01:06:22,630 --> 01:06:23,580
What?

1572
01:06:23,580 --> 01:06:26,690
Seina also ended up giong that way?

1573
01:06:25,970 --> 01:06:27,700
She did?

1574
01:06:28,450 --> 01:06:30,390
Today you win, okay?

1575
01:06:30,390 --> 01:06:32,140
They get along so well.

1576
01:06:33,930 --> 01:06:35,550
It's a horse!

1577
01:06:35,550 --> 01:06:37,410
Don't run!

1578
01:06:37,410 --> 01:06:38,460
It's a horse!

1579
01:06:38,460 --> 01:06:39,550
A horse is there?

1580
01:06:39,550 --> 01:06:41,220
It's a cow, though.

1581
01:06:41,220 --> 01:06:42,720
It was a cow.

1582
01:06:42,720 --> 01:06:44,050
A cow.

1583
01:06:44,050 --> 01:06:47,060
I wonder if we can get a balloon.

1584
01:06:47,310 --> 01:06:51,080
Wonder if Seina understood Nao's wish to get one.

1585
01:06:53,680 --> 01:06:54,910
She did.

1586
01:06:55,820 --> 01:06:57,170
Nao also got one.

1587
01:06:56,780 --> 01:06:57,970
How great.

1588
01:06:58,990 --> 01:07:01,000
Yellow.

1589
01:07:01,020 --> 01:07:03,840
I wanted a pink one.

1590
01:07:03,840 --> 01:07:05,730
Go get one yourself.

1591
01:07:07,240 --> 01:07:09,910
We have to put money in, right?

1592
01:07:09,960 --> 01:07:11,750
Yes, money.

1593
01:07:10,750 --> 01:07:11,750
It's saisen.

1594
01:07:11,750 --> 01:07:14,080
We give all of our money, right?

1595
01:07:14,080 --> 01:07:14,980
No.

1596
01:07:15,330 --> 01:07:17,900
Seina puts 500 yen in.

1597
01:07:18,450 --> 01:07:19,610
And Nao?

1598
01:07:21,540 --> 01:07:22,710
There we go...

1599
01:07:23,130 --> 01:07:24,330
Next...

1600
01:07:24,830 --> 01:07:26,430
It doesn't ring...

1601
01:07:26,430 --> 01:07:27,250
Huh.

1602
01:07:28,160 --> 01:07:29,750
It won't ring.

1603
01:07:28,980 --> 01:07:30,220
He doesn't have the power.

1604
01:07:30,130 --> 01:07:31,700
Seina is thinking.

1605
01:07:33,150 --> 01:07:34,300
Ring ring

1606
01:07:34,300 --> 01:07:36,170
Ring ring ring

1607
01:07:36,170 --> 01:07:37,610
Nao, it rang.

1608
01:07:37,610 --> 01:07:38,940
Okay.

1609
01:07:39,280 --> 01:07:40,610
Okay.

1610
01:07:39,660 --> 01:07:41,190
That was good.

1611
01:07:41,560 --> 01:07:43,810
Let's go. Next is the charm.

1612
01:07:44,100 --> 01:07:45,230
I see.

1613
01:07:45,230 --> 01:07:46,620
Let's get one.

1614
01:07:46,620 --> 01:07:48,680
They will buy a charm.

1615
01:07:50,550 --> 01:07:53,190
What a grand atmosphere.

1616
01:07:55,160 --> 01:07:56,830
It's a wedding.

1617
01:07:57,130 --> 01:07:58,580
How nice.

1618
01:07:58,580 --> 01:08:00,750
To be able to honor your ancestors.

1619
01:08:01,080 --> 01:08:02,930
Thinking that they might stand by and watch...

1620
01:08:03,620 --> 01:08:04,500
It's this one.

1621
01:08:04,500 --> 01:08:06,170
They weren't even watching it.

1622
01:08:05,130 --> 01:08:06,540
Not at all.

1623
01:08:07,300 --> 01:08:08,600
Not even a bit.

1624
01:08:08,600 --> 01:08:10,870
To smoothen things.

1625
01:08:10,870 --> 01:08:11,960
See?

1626
01:08:11,960 --> 01:08:13,240
They can read?

1627
01:08:12,160 --> 01:08:13,340
Let's buy this.

1628
01:08:13,340 --> 01:08:16,210
Seina bought the charm to smoothen things.

1629
01:08:22,390 --> 01:08:26,040
There are so many cute girls.

1630
01:08:26,540 --> 01:08:28,620
He's a boy after all.

1631
01:08:31,480 --> 01:08:34,260
I wanted a pink one.

1632
01:08:34,350 --> 01:08:35,830
He's still harping on that.

1633
01:08:35,900 --> 01:08:38,180
Nao, please don't run, okay?

1634
01:08:38,180 --> 01:08:40,000
Seina is getting tired.

1635
01:08:40,000 --> 01:08:41,370
Dango shop.

1636
01:08:41,370 --> 01:08:43,510
Don't run!

1637
01:08:43,510 --> 01:08:47,040
You were told not to run, weren't you!

1638
01:08:47,040 --> 01:08:48,560
He's being told so many times.

1639
01:08:48,240 --> 01:08:50,680
Nao, you will trip.

1640
01:08:50,730 --> 01:08:51,480
Ah!

1641
01:08:51,480 --> 01:08:53,550
There are so many!

1642
01:08:52,700 --> 01:08:54,030
He's sprinting.

1643
01:08:53,550 --> 01:08:54,980
Cotton candy too.

1644
01:08:54,980 --> 01:08:57,820
Yay, so much.

1645
01:08:57,170 --> 01:08:59,110
The adults can't keep up.

1646
01:08:57,840 --> 01:08:59,520
What about the dango?

1647
01:08:59,520 --> 01:09:00,720
Look!

1648
01:09:00,720 --> 01:09:02,560
Dango.

1649
01:09:02,560 --> 01:09:05,030
There's so much.

1650
01:09:03,160 --> 01:09:05,030
Won't you purchase dango?

1651
01:09:05,030 --> 01:09:07,280
They sell the masks at your home, don't they?

1652
01:09:07,830 --> 01:09:09,750
They were asked to get dango for 5 people.

1653
01:09:09,750 --> 01:09:12,800
Dango, please.

1654
01:09:11,170 --> 01:09:12,800
Dango, please.

1655
01:09:13,240 --> 01:09:15,520
With this kind of money.

1656
01:09:14,370 --> 01:09:16,710
You were given this much money?

1657
01:09:17,140 --> 01:09:18,140
And...?

1658
01:09:18,140 --> 01:09:20,740
3 boxes? 2 boxes?

1659
01:09:20,740 --> 01:09:21,810
Or 5?

1660
01:09:21,280 --> 01:09:24,410
Yep, 5 boxes.

1661
01:09:21,810 --> 01:09:24,800
Wouldn't 5 be a wee too heavy to carry?

1662
01:09:24,800 --> 01:09:27,230
We can.

1663
01:09:25,670 --> 01:09:28,250
I see. Roger that.

1664
01:09:28,600 --> 01:09:30,770
Won't 5 be a bit too heavy?

1665
01:09:30,770 --> 01:09:32,740
Seina is worried.

1666
01:09:33,840 --> 01:09:38,430
We will eat for two.

1667
01:09:38,430 --> 01:09:40,200
And then we bring it to our mamas.

1668
01:09:40,200 --> 01:09:41,530
That would be nice.

1669
01:09:41,030 --> 01:09:42,170
I see...

1670
01:09:42,370 --> 01:09:44,430
They were planning to eat them all there?

1671
01:09:45,250 --> 01:09:48,400
If they both eat and take 3 back with them.

1672
01:09:48,400 --> 01:09:49,910
Looks nice.

1673
01:09:50,210 --> 01:09:53,240
We thought of a nice thing.

1674
01:09:51,720 --> 01:09:53,240
What nice thing?

1675
01:09:53,240 --> 01:09:55,040
If we eat for two and for out moms...

1676
01:09:55,040 --> 01:09:57,040
If we eat for two and for out moms...

1677
01:09:57,040 --> 01:09:58,300
A present?

1678
01:09:57,550 --> 01:09:58,300
Yep.

1679
01:09:58,300 --> 01:10:01,780
I see. You will only eat your portion. Got ya.

1680
01:10:03,720 --> 01:10:05,300
Right?

1681
01:10:06,810 --> 01:10:10,240
For mama and papa, right? I'm writing
a letter to them so please wait.

1682
01:10:10,240 --> 01:10:12,700
She's writing a receipt.

1683
01:10:15,260 --> 01:10:18,000
This old lady will hold them for you so please give them

1684
01:10:18,680 --> 01:10:21,350
since you plan on eating dango first.

1685
01:10:21,570 --> 01:10:24,920
If the wind blows hard they will fly away.

1686
01:10:24,920 --> 01:10:28,230
That's right. Which is why this old lady will hold them.

1687
01:10:28,230 --> 01:10:29,610
Please wait.

1688
01:10:29,050 --> 01:10:32,150
But what if you forget them?

1689
01:10:30,710 --> 01:10:32,150
It's fine. I won't forget.

1690
01:10:32,150 --> 01:10:33,950
He's afraid she will keep them.

1691
01:10:33,950 --> 01:10:37,200
This is your spare change cause you gave me 3000 yen.

1692
01:10:37,200 --> 01:10:40,360
Tell them you purchased 5.

1693
01:10:40,360 --> 01:10:42,560
And the two of you will eat your part, right?

1694
01:10:41,290 --> 01:10:42,560
Wow!

1695
01:10:42,560 --> 01:10:45,440
So this is a freebie for your hard work.

1696
01:10:45,440 --> 01:10:47,250
Since you are such good kids.

1697
01:10:47,250 --> 01:10:48,230
Who understood it?

1698
01:10:48,230 --> 01:10:49,900
We did!

1699
01:10:49,900 --> 01:10:51,430
I love this dango.

1700
01:10:51,430 --> 01:10:53,670
Thank you so much old lady.

1701
01:10:53,670 --> 01:10:55,090
Grace.

1702
01:10:55,990 --> 01:10:57,320
What about saying grace.

1703
01:10:57,320 --> 01:10:59,340
Grace.

1704
01:10:58,070 --> 01:10:59,340
Grace.

1705
01:10:59,340 --> 01:11:01,590
Grace.

1706
01:11:00,060 --> 01:11:01,590
Grace.

1707
01:11:01,590 --> 01:11:04,410
Thanks to you the two of them are enjoying themselves.

1708
01:11:04,150 --> 01:11:05,650
How nice.

1709
01:11:05,800 --> 01:11:08,070
Two warm teas, please.

1710
01:11:09,820 --> 01:11:11,520
He loves dango.

1711
01:11:12,710 --> 01:11:14,860
Um, how delicious.

1712
01:11:15,390 --> 01:11:16,490
Mama is waiting...

1713
01:11:16,490 --> 01:11:20,200
Just like the old lady the dango has a kind taste.

1714
01:11:22,550 --> 01:11:23,780
How nice.

1715
01:11:24,030 --> 01:11:25,970
Is this free service?

1716
01:11:25,180 --> 01:11:25,970
Yes.

1717
01:11:29,420 --> 01:11:30,910
Thanks for the meal.

1718
01:11:30,910 --> 01:11:34,480
Thanks for the meal.

1719
01:11:32,170 --> 01:11:34,480
Thank you very much.

1720
01:11:34,480 --> 01:11:37,650
They properly said "thanks for the meal".

1721
01:11:37,780 --> 01:11:41,620
Since the dango they ate were freebies they are bringing 5 back.

1722
01:11:41,620 --> 01:11:43,570
Cotton candy.

1723
01:11:42,870 --> 01:11:43,970
Looks heavy.

1724
01:11:43,570 --> 01:11:45,670
They have cotton candy and masks.

1725
01:11:45,670 --> 01:11:49,140
Don't they sell lots of masks at the shop where Nao lives?

1726
01:11:51,480 --> 01:11:53,830
You forgot something.

1727
01:11:54,350 --> 01:11:55,830
The balloons!

1728
01:11:55,830 --> 01:11:58,430
This old lady forgot.

1729
01:11:56,820 --> 01:11:58,270
So close.

1730
01:11:57,430 --> 01:11:59,590
Just like he said.

1731
01:11:58,280 --> 01:11:59,590
They did forget it.

1732
01:11:59,590 --> 01:12:04,170
I can only hold 2.

1733
01:12:01,140 --> 01:12:04,170
Hold 1 and she will hold 1.

1734
01:12:04,170 --> 01:12:08,640
Glad she didn't have to chase them down the stairs.

1735
01:12:06,790 --> 01:12:08,860
Excuse me.

1736
01:12:08,860 --> 01:12:11,110
How many yen are these?

1737
01:12:11,110 --> 01:12:12,580
One is 100 yen.

1738
01:12:12,580 --> 01:12:14,480
I will get one for 100 yen.

1739
01:12:14,480 --> 01:12:16,790
Despite them selling so many at home.

1740
01:12:17,300 --> 01:12:19,190
It's still tempting.

1741
01:12:18,850 --> 01:12:22,060
Not the blue, he likes the red one.

1742
01:12:22,730 --> 01:12:25,040
I will get this one.

1743
01:12:25,280 --> 01:12:27,760
They have those at home too.

1744
01:12:28,200 --> 01:12:30,170
Must be different to him.

1745
01:12:32,900 --> 01:12:34,400
It's so loud.

1746
01:12:36,540 --> 01:12:38,210
Want to do it?

1747
01:12:42,600 --> 01:12:45,750
This is the smaller slope of higashisando.

1748
01:12:45,430 --> 01:12:46,780
Please go slow.

1749
01:12:46,330 --> 01:12:48,100
The cameramen are tired too.

1750
01:12:50,670 --> 01:12:53,460
Huh, what's going on?

1751
01:12:53,460 --> 01:12:55,310
It's fine. Thanks.

1752
01:12:55,310 --> 01:12:56,810
He called out to the cameraman.

1753
01:12:56,810 --> 01:12:59,500
This one is so loud.

1754
01:12:59,500 --> 01:13:01,180
Nice chance. Make use of the time.

1755
01:13:04,350 --> 01:13:06,670
Meanwhile the cameramen are running ahead.

1756
01:13:08,500 --> 01:13:09,840
This must be tough.

1757
01:13:10,820 --> 01:13:11,820
Wait.

1758
01:13:11,970 --> 01:13:13,010
Wait.

1759
01:13:13,990 --> 01:13:16,330
We were able to get a shot from the front.

1760
01:13:16,330 --> 01:13:18,500
Nao, you might trip.

1761
01:13:19,870 --> 01:13:22,170
Our mamas must be worrying.

1762
01:13:24,890 --> 01:13:29,640
Errand errand how fun.

1763
01:13:30,740 --> 01:13:32,500
A dango order coming up.

1764
01:13:32,500 --> 01:13:34,330
It's Shiro from next door.

1765
01:13:35,950 --> 01:13:38,770
Shiro you can't eat the dango.

1766
01:13:39,620 --> 01:13:41,340
He's not even saying anything.

1767
01:13:41,690 --> 01:13:43,320
Go... errand...

1768
01:13:43,320 --> 01:13:45,720
They've arrived home.

1769
01:13:46,380 --> 01:13:48,840
I'm tired by now.

1770
01:13:47,410 --> 01:13:48,840
Yeah.

1771
01:13:52,030 --> 01:13:55,230
They didn't fall once and now that they are here.

1772
01:13:56,640 --> 01:13:58,200
Oh no, the tama-kons.

1773
01:13:59,670 --> 01:14:01,520
The tama-kons...

1774
01:14:01,290 --> 01:14:02,790
It's fine if they just wash it.

1775
01:14:02,860 --> 01:14:07,250
Mothers, the two of them did it all the way without any hiccups.

1776
01:14:10,530 --> 01:14:11,850
Let's wash and eat them.

1777
01:14:11,850 --> 01:14:14,620
Since the soy sauce has permeated it.

1778
01:14:14,800 --> 01:14:18,220
Did you buy a charm?

1779
01:14:16,410 --> 01:14:18,220
What's with this balloon?

1780
01:14:18,220 --> 01:14:19,810
How come?

1781
01:14:20,980 --> 01:14:22,290
Did you buy it?

1782
01:14:23,000 --> 01:14:24,300
Let's eat them together!

1783
01:14:24,300 --> 01:14:26,650
Nao is the one who settled things.

1784
01:14:26,650 --> 01:14:27,970
It's delicious.

1785
01:14:28,720 --> 01:14:32,090
I ate one of these.

1786
01:14:32,090 --> 01:14:33,720
Did you eat dango there?

1787
01:14:34,410 --> 01:14:36,360
Huh. How unfair.

1788
01:14:36,360 --> 01:14:40,850
They went on their first errand in 2008.

1789
01:14:40,850 --> 01:14:43,170
9 years later

1790
01:14:43,170 --> 01:14:44,880
from the errand when they were 3.

1791
01:14:44,880 --> 01:14:48,950
Shiogama was hit by the Great East Japan Earthquake

1792
01:14:49,090 --> 01:14:51,570
People had to evacuate to the hilltop shrine.

1793
01:14:52,220 --> 01:14:55,980
Seina and her family moved to Kanagawa prefecture after the earthquake.

1794
01:14:55,980 --> 01:14:59,100
In all those years it's the first time that she has returned.

1795
01:15:01,380 --> 01:15:05,170
First year students of junior high school.

1796
01:15:03,290 --> 01:15:05,700
Seriously?

1797
01:15:04,600 --> 01:15:05,700
They've become so big.

1798
01:15:05,840 --> 01:15:07,390
They still get along.

1799
01:15:08,960 --> 01:15:11,910
It rings this time.

1800
01:15:12,800 --> 01:15:17,530
Their moms are best friends so they'll always have a connection.

1801
01:15:19,540 --> 01:15:22,570
Since they've come all this way they better get a charm to smoothen things.

1802
01:15:22,570 --> 01:15:24,810
How nice.

1803
01:15:26,340 --> 01:15:30,310
As junior high students what do they wish will go well?

1804
01:15:30,560 --> 01:15:32,620
What do you wish will go well?

1805
01:15:32,620 --> 01:15:34,330
Club activity and study.

1806
01:15:34,330 --> 01:15:35,320
Study?

1807
01:15:35,320 --> 01:15:36,770
Studying doesn't matter.

1808
01:15:36,770 --> 01:15:40,640
What's he saying? Actually Nao is performing well in his studies.

1809
01:15:41,270 --> 01:15:43,660
He's completely into tennis after school.

1810
01:15:49,500 --> 01:15:52,370
"Please, only edit in the good parts" he told us.

1811
01:15:54,890 --> 01:15:57,020
Something he's more into is...

1812
01:15:57,020 --> 01:16:00,860
He wants to become a pâtisserie when he grows up.

1813
01:16:02,060 --> 01:16:06,230
Once he heard that Seina was coming he's been making cakes since morning.

1814
01:16:09,870 --> 01:16:12,220
With various decorations.

1815
01:16:12,220 --> 01:16:13,370
So?

1816
01:16:13,370 --> 01:16:16,040
Wonder which one is for Seina.

1817
01:16:17,080 --> 01:16:19,550
Huh? One of them is special.

1818
01:16:22,800 --> 01:16:24,900
This one is for Seina.

1819
01:16:24,900 --> 01:16:28,200
It's actually Seina's birthday tomorrow.

1820
01:16:28,390 --> 01:16:32,270
Surprising her with two gifts, eh? I see...

1821
01:16:32,910 --> 01:16:33,790
Amazing.

1822
01:16:33,790 --> 01:16:37,010
Seina is in the brass-band club.

1823
01:16:37,010 --> 01:16:39,930
She's playing the biggest instrument: The tuba.

1824
01:16:39,050 --> 01:16:40,220
Looks heavy.

1825
01:16:40,220 --> 01:16:43,490
After trying out several students she was able to play it best.

1826
01:16:44,220 --> 01:16:46,740
She's been playing since junior high school.

1827
01:16:46,740 --> 01:16:49,540
Before that was karate, gymnastics, swimming.

1828
01:16:49,540 --> 01:16:54,480
An instrument that requires force and lung capacity. A true match for Seina.

1829
01:16:56,580 --> 01:16:59,050
To carry a 10 kilo tuba lightly

1830
01:16:59,440 --> 01:17:01,240
That's heavy.

1831
01:17:01,350 --> 01:17:04,610
and to make it look fun during performances.

1832
01:17:05,720 --> 01:17:08,380
She's practicing that right now.

1833
01:17:10,430 --> 01:17:14,030
During the earthquake, it caused a tsunami so great...

1834
01:17:14,030 --> 01:17:16,900
that it carried tour boats, docked in the marina, onto land.

1835
01:17:17,100 --> 01:17:19,970
The two don't bring those times up.

1836
01:17:20,270 --> 01:17:23,510
The dango shop used to be right there.

1837
01:17:23,510 --> 01:17:24,330
And then...

1838
01:17:24,560 --> 01:17:26,500
You sure grew up.

1839
01:17:26,650 --> 01:17:29,050
The old lady has also become quite old.

1840
01:17:29,250 --> 01:17:31,720
It's been a long time.

1841
01:17:31,900 --> 01:17:34,200
How has everything been?

1842
01:17:33,400 --> 01:17:34,200
Good.

1843
01:17:34,670 --> 01:17:37,170
It's been such a long time since you tried my oden.

1844
01:17:37,170 --> 01:17:39,340
These oden will be a freebie.

1845
01:17:39,340 --> 01:17:41,390
Thank you very much.

1846
01:17:40,510 --> 01:17:43,280
Thank you for coming and visiting me.

1847
01:17:44,980 --> 01:17:47,150
I've made these.

1848
01:17:47,150 --> 01:17:49,590
He decided they will eat them at the dango shop.

1849
01:17:49,590 --> 01:17:50,850
Amazing.

1850
01:17:50,850 --> 01:17:53,120
Please eat the one you like.

1851
01:17:55,790 --> 01:17:57,210
I don't know if they taste good.

1852
01:17:57,330 --> 01:17:58,760
Incredibly delicious.

1853
01:18:00,000 --> 01:18:02,360
He won't give her the birthday special?

1854
01:18:01,880 --> 01:18:03,130
Huh. That's true.

1855
01:18:03,770 --> 01:18:05,230
What about the birthday present?

1856
01:18:05,230 --> 01:18:07,300
I forgot to bring it.

1857
01:18:07,300 --> 01:18:08,690
That can't be.

1858
01:18:08,690 --> 01:18:09,960
It finally came out.

1859
01:18:09,960 --> 01:18:10,910
Really?

1860
01:18:11,060 --> 01:18:14,740
Can't be helped. And he woke up early because of it.

1861
01:18:15,240 --> 01:18:16,950
When we get back.

1862
01:18:16,150 --> 01:18:16,950
When we get back?

1863
01:18:17,310 --> 01:18:19,620
This is Naoki who hasn't changed.

1864
01:18:19,300 --> 01:18:21,100
What was he thinking?

1865
01:18:19,830 --> 01:18:21,100
At such an important time.

1866
01:18:21,120 --> 01:18:23,600
His store managed to be spared, but...

1867
01:18:23,600 --> 01:18:28,540
the seawater came up to waist height and many of the shops were severely damaged.

1868
01:18:29,210 --> 01:18:30,180
This. This.

1869
01:18:30,180 --> 01:18:31,990
The important thing.

1870
01:18:34,150 --> 01:18:38,300
It's a bit early but happy birthday.

1871
01:18:36,670 --> 01:18:38,300
Thank you very much.

1872
01:18:38,300 --> 01:18:41,200
It's made from choco-chip banana.

1873
01:18:41,200 --> 01:18:43,210
Thank you very much.

1874
01:18:43,210 --> 01:18:45,120
Why are you speaking so formal?

1875
01:18:45,120 --> 01:18:48,610
This awkward distance is normal for first year junior high students.

1876
01:18:48,610 --> 01:18:50,610
Nice.

1877
01:18:53,200 --> 01:18:56,100
I got really nervous.

1878
01:18:56,320 --> 01:19:03,080
Just like Naoki all boys that age when they get excited they run around a lot.

1879
01:19:03,080 --> 01:19:05,790
She told him: "Don't run!"

1880
01:19:05,790 --> 01:19:07,560
He's so energetic.

1881
01:19:07,560 --> 01:19:10,050
Apropos Miyagi Prefecture, Sandwich Man you...

1882
01:19:09,050 --> 01:19:10,970
That's right, it's my home area.

1883
01:19:10,050 --> 01:19:12,030
Yeah, your home area.

1884
01:19:10,970 --> 01:19:12,030
I often go to Shiogama.

1885
01:19:12,230 --> 01:19:14,170
Does it bring up some memories?

1886
01:19:14,170 --> 01:19:19,320
When I was in kindergarten and living in Ishinomaki

1887
01:19:19,320 --> 01:19:22,580
there was a butcher not close by.

1888
01:19:22,750 --> 01:19:25,010
I was told to go get 500 g. minced meat.

1889
01:19:25,310 --> 01:19:26,520
I went by myself.

1890
01:19:26,520 --> 01:19:28,200
And when I arrived at the butcher

1891
01:19:28,200 --> 01:19:30,590
I said: "Please give me 500 g. of muscle."

1892
01:19:33,160 --> 01:19:37,460
I was told to go back and ask again.

1893
01:19:37,460 --> 01:19:41,450
And on the way back there was a big street that I had to cross.

1894
01:19:41,450 --> 01:19:44,970
And as I put my hand up to cross a taxi stopped by.

1895
01:19:46,590 --> 01:19:47,840
When a child rasies their hands

1896
01:19:47,840 --> 01:19:50,120
it's not to hail a ride.

1897
01:19:50,970 --> 01:19:53,310
I remember it vividly.

1898
01:19:53,380 --> 01:19:57,730
What do you think about the chance
if your kid could go on an errand?

1899
01:19:57,730 --> 01:20:00,830
I want to let them but I'm also afraid.

1900
01:20:00,830 --> 01:20:04,390
I would probably dress up like the staff here and follow him.

1901
01:20:04,940 --> 01:20:09,040
Yeah, the parents must be so worried.

1902
01:20:07,660 --> 01:20:09,040
That's right.

1903
01:20:09,660 --> 01:20:13,200
But there will be a day when they
have to be allowed out on their own.

1904
01:20:13,200 --> 01:20:17,950
A father who has made this decision is here today.

1905
01:20:17,950 --> 01:20:20,730
Special Guest will appear

1906
01:20:17,950 --> 01:20:20,740
Everyone, let's welcome him.

1907
01:20:20,740 --> 01:20:24,040
Papa, please enter this way.

1908
01:20:24,040 --> 01:20:25,840
Please enter.

1909
01:20:28,660 --> 01:20:32,870
Pro-boxing's former WBC World Bantamweight Champion

1910
01:20:32,870 --> 01:20:36,770
Yamanaka Shinsuke.

1911
01:20:37,990 --> 01:20:40,390
